content.text: Variables \(x\) and \(y\) are such that, when \(\sqrt[4]{y}\) is plotted against \(\frac{1}{x}\), a straight line graph passing through the points (0.5, 9) and (3, 34) is obtained. Find \(y\) as a function of \(x\)
Write \(9x^{2} - 12x + 5\) in the form \(p(x - q)^{2} + r\), where \(p\), \(q\) and \(r\) are constants
Hence write down the coordinates of the minimum point of the curve \(y = 9x^{2} - 12x + 5\)
Find the remainder when \(\mathrm{p}(x)\) is divided by \(x + 1\)
Show that \(x + 2\) is a factor of \(\mathrm{p}(x)\)
Write \(\mathrm{p}(x)\) as a product of linear factors
**DO NOT USE A CALCULATOR IN THIS QUESTION.**
In an examination, candidates must select 2 questions from the 5 questions in section A and select 4 questions from the 8 questions in section B. Find the number of ways in which this can be done
The digits of the number 6 378 129 are to be arranged so that the resulting 7-digit number is even. Find the number of ways in which this can be done
Find the value of each of the constants \(\alpha\) and \(\beta\) such that \(4\mathbf{a} - \mathbf{b} = (\alpha +3)\mathbf{i} - 2\mathbf{j}\)
Hence find the unit vector in the direction of \(\mathbf{b} - 4\mathbf{a}\)
The vectors \(\mathbf{a}\) and \(\mathbf{b}\) are such that \(\mathbf{a} = \alpha \mathbf{i} + \mathbf{j}\) and \(\mathbf{b} = 12\mathbf{i} + \beta \mathbf{j}\)
Find the values of \(k\) for which the line \(y = kx - 7\) and the curve \(y = 3x^{2} + 8x + 5\) do not intersect
Solve the simultaneous equations
giving \(x\) and \(y\) in exact simplified form
Expand \((2 - x)^{5}\), simplifying each coefficient
Hence solve \(\frac{\mathrm{e}^{(2 - x)^5} \times \mathrm{e}^{80x}}{\mathrm{e}^{10x^4 + 32}} = \mathrm{e}^{-x^5}\)
Sketch the velocity-time graph for this journey on the axes below
Find the distance between \(O\) and \(A\)
Find the deceleration in the last 5 seconds

A particle travels in a straight line. As it passes through a fixed point \(O\), the particle is travelling at a velocity of \(3 \mathrm{~m} \mathrm{s}^{- 1}\). The particle continues at this velocity for 60 seconds then decelerates at a constant rate for 15 seconds to a velocity of \(1.6 \mathrm{~m} \mathrm{s}^{- 1}\). The particle then decelerates again at a constant rate for 5 seconds to reach point \(A\), where it stops
Find the value of \(a\) and of \(b\)
Find the area of the shaded region

The diagram shows part of the graphs of \(y = 4x^{\frac{2}{3}}\) and \(y = (x - 3)^2\). The graph of \(y = (x - 3)^2\) meets the \(x\)-axis at the point \(A(a, 0)\) and the two graphs intersect at the point \(B(b, 4)\)
Sketch the graph of \(y = \mathrm{f}(x)\) and hence sketch the graph of \(y = \mathrm{f}^{-1}(x)\) on the axes below
Find an expression for \(\mathrm{g}^{-1}(x)\) and state its domain and range
Find and simplify an expression for \(\mathrm{fg}(x)\)
Explain why the function gf does not exist
The function g is defined by \(\mathrm{g}(x) = (x - 4)^2 + 1\) for \(x \leqslant 4\)
The function f is defined by \(\mathrm{f}(x) = \ln (2x + 1)\) for \(x \geqslant 0\)
Find the \(x\)-coordinates of the stationary points of the curve \(y = \mathrm{e}^{3x}(2x + 3)^6.\)

A curve has equation \(y = \mathrm{f}(x)\) and has exactly two stationary points. Given that \(\mathrm{f}''(x) = 4x - 7\), \(\mathrm{f}'(0.5) = 0\) and \(\mathrm{f}'(3) = 0\), use the second derivative test to determine the nature of each of the stationary points of this curve
In this question all lengths are in centimetres

The diagram shows a solid cuboid with height \(h\) and a rectangular base measuring \(4x\) by \(x\). The volume of the cuboid is \(40 \text{cm}^3\). Given that \(x\) and \(h\) can vary and that the surface area of the cuboid has a minimum value, find this value
